    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.15.37" />
                <note type="curatorial">179 House Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">37</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                ST. LOUIS POST-DISPATCH
                <lb/>
                
                "OF MAKING MANY BOOKS"
                <lb/>
                JOHN G. NEIHARDT
                <lb/>
                
                BRANSON, MISSOURI
                </fw>
                
                
                
                <opener>
                <dateline>Tuesday A. M.</dateline>
                
                
                
                <salute><hi rend="italic">Dear</hi> Comrade:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>That's a devil of a hard break, and I'm more sorry than I can say! I wish I could be with you while you are laid up. Your note indicates that you are standing it with your accustomed philosophic good sense, which I sometimes envy you. Anyway, here's love, best of Comrades. I suppose you will be able to keep the magazine going by using a stenographer.</p>
                <closer>
                <salute>Always yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Jno.</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                
                <ab type="postmark">BRANSON APR 7 1 - PM 1931 MO.</ab>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
